rComments: One of the best Profs I've had so far, Jess is so kind, quirky, and fun to learn from! She doesn't post lectures on Quercus which means you have to show up to class, but it's fun in class so don't worry! Class itself was easy, just do the short readings and Jess does all the close reading work for you in class :)
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I've had Jess in a couple different classes and she is by far my favourite instructor. As long as you follow the instructions and note her grading criteria, you'll do fine. She's such a cool person, very thoughtful, and flexible with due dates. She makes me feel more confident in my writing. I'd take any class she teaches/ tas!

She is an amazing Prof! her lectures were insightful, interesting, and interactive. The course load is expected for a 300 level English course, but her grading criteria is extremely clear. She is very flexible on extensions and genuinely cares about her students. I wish she taught more courses at UTM. No doubt, I would take future classes with her
Henderson was pretty easy to listen to during lecture, but definitely lays on the work heavy. Also a TOUGH marker. Have had her as my Ta a few times and as a prof she is challenging
